<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written Submission to the Energy and Climate Change Committee Inquiry on the IPCC Fifth Assessment Report, Working Group I, The Physical Science Basis</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by Dr Ruth Dixon (IPC0023)</span></p><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I am submitting this evidence on the subject of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">scrutiny and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">review of the IPCC report. I am not associated with the IPCC </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and my evidence is drawn from published sources</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. I have undertaken academic research and teaching at the Universi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ty of Oxford since 19</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">86. I am the author or </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">co-author</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> over 50 peer-reviewed publications </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the natural sciences (</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">c</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">hemistry and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">b</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">iochemistry) and the social sciences. I have also reviewed numerous papers for academic journals. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The views in this evidence are my own, and do </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">not represent the views of my employer or any other organization.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">The Review Process for IPCC Reports</span></p><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Summary</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The IPCC </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">eports </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">are</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the most authoritative and up-to-date </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">assessment</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of the science </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">of climate change that we have, and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">are</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> valuable to policy makers and their advisers as they seek to frame policy regarding climate change. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> IPCC reports</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">have</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> been </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">described </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">as </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">among </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the most heavily scrutinised documents in the history of science</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">’</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and IPCC officials </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">emphasise the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">‘process of rigorous peer reviews’</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> tha</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">t the reports undergo</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">n my opinion</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, however,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the IPCC reports cannot be described as ‘peer-reviewed’.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">n this evidence </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">explain why</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> scrutiny does not correspond </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to peer-</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">review</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> as is normally understood by the term</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, but is more like a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">process</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">public comment</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Although a large number of comments are received and each must be responded to, the response </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">of IPCC authors has</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> very often </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">been </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to dismiss critical comments.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Review </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">E</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ditors are appointed </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">by the IPCC </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to oversee the review process</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> for each chapter</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">but </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">this</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">did</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">not ensure that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">all </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">review </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">comments </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">we</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">re </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">responded to appropriately</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> nor that the full range of scientific views were represented</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> in the Fourth Assessment Report (AR4)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. I</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">t remains to be seen whether the Review Editors played a larger part in the Fifth Assessment Report (AR5).</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">If the IPCC reports are to be seen as </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">truly </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">authoritative, a far more challenging review process should be i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">nstituted</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. This could take the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">form of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">‘Red Team’ </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in which</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> experts from other scientific disciplines </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">would be</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> commissioned to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">undertake a critical review of the IPCC reports, in whole or in part.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">My evidence is in three parts. Part A describes the IPCC r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">eview process and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">explains </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">how it differs from conventional </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">academic </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">peer-review. Part B </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">documents </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">similar</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> criticisms by the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">independent </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">InterAcademy Review </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">IPCC </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">procedures </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in 2010</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">describes </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the responses of the IPCC to that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">eview. Part C </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">sums up </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the prospects for AR5</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and future reports</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ul><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">My evidence addresses the Committee’s questions: </span></p><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Has the IPCC adequately addressed criticisms of previous reports?</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">’ and </span></p><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">‘</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">To what extent does AR5 reflect the range of views among climate scientists?</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">’</span></p><ol type="A" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 16.67pt; padding-left:1.18pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The IPCC </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Review Process</span></li></ol><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The IPCC reports are described by the IPCC and others as subject to extensive review. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">An IPCC press flyer for the Fourth Assessment Report (AR4) referred to ‘2500+ expert </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">reviewers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">’</span><a name="_ftnref3"></a><a href="#_ftn3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Thomas Stocker, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">co-</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">chair of Working Group I (WGI)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> said</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the Fifth Assessment Report (AR5)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I know of no other </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">d</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ocument that has been </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">reviewed in such a thorough way</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">’</span><a name="_ftnref4"></a><a href="#_ftn4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Despite these assurances, r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">eaders of the IPCC reports should be aware that the reports </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">do not undergo</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> what is conventionally understood by academic peer-review, for instance of a scientific paper submitted to a journal. In normal </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">scientific </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">peer-review the (usually anonymous) reviewers have a major influence as to whether a paper is accepted for publicati</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">on, and can </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">generally</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> insist on substantial change</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s to the content of the paper. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Reviewers </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">decide whether the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> author</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">’ changes</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">meet their requirements</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he journal editor has the final say as to whether the authors have made an appropriate response. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e reviewers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">of IPCC reports are in a very different position</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in that</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> when they </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">have submitted their comments</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> their role in the process </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">essentially </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ends.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Reviewers are </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">able</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to comment on the First Order Drafts and the Second Order Drafts of the IPCC reports. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">This process le</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">d</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">tens of thousands</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of comments </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">from reviewers with a wide range of expertise. Each comment must be responded to by chapter authors, as stipulated by</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the IPCC procedures. However, IPCC</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> authors can reject the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> comments with a brief justification which the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">review</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">er</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> has no opportunity </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to challenge – or </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">even to read</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">until</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the review comments are released</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, some time after the final report i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s published</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. The </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">review</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> can only judge the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">authors’ </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">response</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">by </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">comparing the text with the next (or final) version of the IPCC report. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Reviewers do not have an opportunity to comment on the final text, which in several places in AR4 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(and at least one place in AR5, WGI</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">contained </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">new </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">material </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">inserted</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> after the end of the review process. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">For these reasons, the IPCC’s review process is more like a system of public comment than peer-review, and the ‘reviewers’ might more accurately be described as ‘commenters’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The imbalance </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">this process</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in favour of the authors </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">over the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">review</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ers </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">is almost</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> complete. Introduction of any changes relies entirely on the authors overcoming their </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">understandable </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">preference for their own text </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">– often describing their own or </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">their </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">col</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">leagues’ work – </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">over</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the suggestions of their critics. Contrary to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the normal process of peer-review, the authors kn</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">o</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">w the identity of each reviewer.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">review comments </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and author responses </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">for</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> AR4</span><a name="_ftnref5"></a><a href="#_ftn5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> showed that authors made very few changes of interpretation or </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">substantive </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">content</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> in response to comments</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, although they often accepted minor (e.g.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> grammatical or typographic) corrections</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> suggestions for clarifying or rearranging the content</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">A</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ltern</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ative interpretations or suggestions for additional literature citations were often summ</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">arily dismissed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">One or more</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Review E</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ditors </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">are</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">appointed by the IPCC </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">for</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> each chapter. They</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">have nominal </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">responsibility to ensure the authors respond appropriately to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> comments</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and that the range of scientific viewpoints are </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">reflected</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">but </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">they apparently rarely exercised their authority in support of reviewers for AR4.</span><a name="_ftnref6"></a><a href="#_ftn6">[6]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">There is no </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">public </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">information ye</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">t </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">about</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">activities </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">of Review Editors </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">for</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> AR5</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The IPCC review </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">process is open to anyone who c</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">hooses to take part. Reviewers </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">are self-selected</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and anyone can become an IPCC reviewer by completing an online registration process. An advantage of this system is that it exposes the draft reports to a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">wide </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">range of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">viewpoi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">nts</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and expertise. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he review comments reveal much careful and thoughtful reflection on the text by a wide range of reviewers. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">However, as r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">eviewers choose the sections of the text on</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> which they wish to comment</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">no</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">-o</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ne is assigned </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> particular section</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to review</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">is process </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">does not</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> ensure that every </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">section </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">is in fact </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">review</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The IPCC review process depends critically on the integrity and diligence of individuals involved, in particular </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Lead Authors and Review Editors</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. Many extremely dedicated ind</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ividuals take part in the production of IPCC reports</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">usually</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> alongside their other </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">professional </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">responsibilities</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">review </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">process is incredibly time-consuming for authors, who are required to respond to every comment</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">But t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">IPCC </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">procedures </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">themselves </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">do not ensure th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">at</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">authors </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">R</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">eview </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">E</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ditors </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">exercise this </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">integrity</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">While certain changes have been made to IPCC procedures since AR4, as discussed below, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I have seen no evidence that the process has changed significantly for AR5</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, though this</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> will not be possible to assess properly</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> until the review comments for AR5 are released.</span></li></ol><ol start="2" type="A" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 16pt; padding-left:2pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">InterAcademy Review</span><a name="_ftnref7"></a><a href="#_ftn7">[7]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> and the IPCC’s response.</span></li></ol><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I now turn to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the InterAcademy Review</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of the IPCC</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. This was a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">n independent review of IPCC procedures conducted in 201</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">0 by the InterAcademy Council (IAC) at the request of the United Nations Environment Programme (UNEP) and the IPCC</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">From the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">IAC Review</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">: </span></li></ol><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">This independent review of the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC) was undertaken by the InterAcademy</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> Council (IAC) under a $950,000 contract signed in April 2010 with the United Nations Environment Programme (UNEP)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">’  </span></p><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">IAC Review</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Committee convened for the purpose comprised twelve experts under the chairmanship of Harold Shapiro, professor of economi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">cs and public affairs at Princeton University, USA.</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">IAC Review</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">commended the IPCC reports and the dedication of the scientists involved in writing them, but identified shortcomings </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">throughout</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">IPCC’s </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">processes and procedures. The conclusion to chapter 2 (p.25) said: </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">significant improvements are both possible and necessary for the fifth assessment and beyond.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">’</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Regarding the IPCC review process</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">IAC </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Review</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> note</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">d</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in chapter 2 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">that</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">although there was no requirement to give every </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">scientific </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">viewpoint equal weight</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Coordinating Lead Authors and Lead Authors have considerable influence over which viewpoints will be discussed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Having</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">author teams with diverse viewpoints is the first st</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">ep toward ensuring that</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">a full range of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">thoughtful views are considered. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Equally important is combating confirmation bias—the tendency of authors to place too much weight on their own views relative to other views [</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">citation</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">]</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> As pointed out to the Committe</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">e by a presenter and some questionnaire respondents, alternative views are not always cited in a chapter if the Lead Authors do not agree with them. Getting the balance right is an ongoing struggle.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> </span></p><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The review recommended that</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Lead Authors should </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">explicitly document that a range of scientific viewpoints has been considered, and  coordinating Lead Authors and Review Editors should satisfy themselves that due consideration was given to properly documented alternative views</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">’</span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">IAC Review</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> noted that</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> over 90,000 comments were received for AR4, and responding to every comment was an onerous task for chapter authors. But </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">it</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> also noted that this process did not ensure a consistent level of scrutiny across the whole IPCC report</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and that authors </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">did not always respond adequately to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">review comments. The </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">IAC Review</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> recommended </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the process should </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">both </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">be radically streamlined, with comments separated into editorial </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">corrections </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and substantive criticisms</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and suggestions</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">IAC Review</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> made some</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> trenchant comments about the role of Review Editors: </span></li></ol><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">A near-universal observation—made in presentations, interviews, and responses to the questionnaire—was the need to strengthen the authority of the Review Editors to ensure that authors consider the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">review comments carefully and document their responses. With a tight schedule for completing revisions, authors do not always do an adequate job of revising the text, and Review Editors do not always require an explanation for rejected comments. In the cas</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">e of the incorrect projection of the disappearance of the Himalayan glaciers, for example, some of the review comments were not adequately considered and the justifications were not completely explained (see Box 2.1). Although a few errors are likely to be</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> missed in any review process, stronger enforcement of existing IPCC procedures by the Review Editors could minimize their number. This includes paying special attention to review comments that point out contradictions, unreferenced literature, or potentia</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">l errors; and ensuring that alternate views receive proper consideration.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">’ </span></p><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The IAC Review</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> recommend</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> that the role of Review Editors should be strengthened, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">but</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> noted </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">that even if that were done ‘</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">it would not make the review process truly independent bec</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">ause the Working Group Co-chairs, who have overall responsibility for the preparation of the reports, are also responsible for selecting Review Editors.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">’ </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The IAC Review suggested that the IPCC should consider instituting a completely independent review pro</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">cess.</span><a name="_ftnref8"></a><a href="#_ftn8">[8]</a></p><ol start="14" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">IPCC</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">discussed the IAC Review at several </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">essions in 2010 and 2011, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">set up four task forces, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and nominally accepted all of its recommendations.</span><a name="_ftnref9"></a><a href="#_ftn9">[9]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> However, the IPCC’s </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">published </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">procedures regarding the review process have in fact changed little.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The IPCC’s procedures are set out in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">‘Appendix A to the Principles Governing IPCC Work’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> (</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">‘the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Principles’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">of which </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">most recent version is dated 2013</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and a previous version is from 2008</span><a name="_ftnref10"></a><a href="#_ftn10">[10]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">relevant </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">section </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">of the Principles </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Section </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">4.3.4) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">only three </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">changes were made</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">concerning the review process</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li><ol type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 67.33pt; padding-left:4.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">co-chairs of the Working Groups </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">should</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> ‘[seek] to ensure complete coverage of all content’; </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 68pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the Working Group bureaux ‘shall actively undertake to promote and invite as wide a group of experts </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">as possible [as reviewers]’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 67.33pt; padding-left:4.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the number of Review Editors should be </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">increased</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> from ‘one to two’ to ‘two to four’ per chapter. </span></li></ol></ol><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 21.3pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The 2013 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">version of the Principles is</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> in some ways less specific than the earlier version</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">F</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">or instance, the 2008 version sa</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">d</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> that ‘</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he review circulation should include: Experts who have significant expertise and/or publications in particular areas covered by the Report’ while the 2013 version simply mention</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> ‘as wide a group of experts as possible.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 21.3pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he IAC’s recommendations </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">for</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">streamlining</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the review process for authors</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> w</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ere</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> not acted upon</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 21.3pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">No changes were made to the role, powers or remit of Review Editors</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he 2013 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">IPCC </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Principles </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(like the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">2008</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> version) emphasised that ‘responsibility for the fina</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">l tex</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">t remains with the Lead Authors</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">’</span></p><ol start="16" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The comments of the Review Editors</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">for AR4 W</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">orking </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">G</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">roup</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">II</span><a name="_ftnref11"></a><a href="#_ftn11">[11]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, showed that only a handful commented on the authors</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> responses </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to comments </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in any detail. Most </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Review Editors </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">simply signed a form letter confirming that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the review procedures had been complied with</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Both </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">2013</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">2008</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">versions of the Principles said: ‘Review Editors will need to ensure that where significant differences of opinion on scientific issues remain, such differences are described in an annex </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to the Report’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> but</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I am unaware of any such annexes being produced for either AR4 or (WGI of) AR5</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span></li></ol><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">C</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> Prospects for AR5</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Future Reports</span></p><ol start="17" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">It was claimed that AR4 was </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">rigorously reviewed, and the same claims are being made about AR5. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">As my evidence above </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">shows</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">however, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the IPCC’s review procedures do not ensure that every section of the report undergoes review</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">n</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">or that substantive criticisms of the text are taken into account. The IPCC reports </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">therefore </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">cannot be considered to be ‘peer-reviewed’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> in the n</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ormal sense</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, despite the time-consuming and complex procedure that currently exists.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">While certain changes were made to the published IPCC </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">procedures</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> (the ‘Principles’) as outlined in paragraph 15 above, it is clear from the IAC Review that the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">procedures </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">were</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> not fully c</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">omplied with in the case of AR4 and i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">t remains to be seen whether </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the same will </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">be the case for</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> AR5</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The number of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">R</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">eview </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">E</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ditors has been increased</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> presumably </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> response to the IAC’s recommendation to strengthen their role in the review process. At least 3 Review Editors </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">are listed in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> each chapter of AR5 WGI.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">However</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Review Editors are not </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">really </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">‘independent’ of the author teams. They are drawn from the same po</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ol of exp</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ertise as Lead Authors. T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">here is no reason to expect that they will </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">tend</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to support the views of reviewers over those o</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">f the authors.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">If the IPCC reports </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">are </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to be seen as truly authoritative, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the IPCC </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">should institute some sort of ‘</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">R</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">eam</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> review</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> by scientists</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, statisticians</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">other </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">experts </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">from </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">outside the climate field, to bring the rigour and expertise of other scien</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">tific disciplines</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">bear on reviewing </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">these important reports</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Such </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">team would </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">have the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">tas</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">k</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">challenging the reports in order to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">identify significant weaknesses</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in balance or content, if they can</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">If it was not practicable to review the whole of the three Working Group reports in this way, certain particularly policy-relevant chapters could be cho</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">sen. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The IPCC </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">itself </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">made use of this type of process </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in 2010 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">when the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> IPCC</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and UNEP</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> c</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ommission</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">independent </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">IAC Review into </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">IPCC </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">procedures</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> at a cost of almost $1 million. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">This approach would seem to be at least as worthwhile to apply to the IPCC </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">reports themselves, which inform such far-reaching policies</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> worldwide</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">December 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> For instance, by the Australian Department of the Environment </span><a href="http://www.climatechange.gov.au/understanding-climate-change/finding-reliable-information-about-climate-science"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.climatechange.gov.au/understanding-climate-change/finding-reliable-information-about-climate-science</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> Speech by Raje</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">ndra Pachauri</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">, IPCC Chair,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> 2008 </span><a href="http://www.ipcc.ch/graphics/speeches/pachauri-davos-january-2008.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.ipcc.ch/graphics/speeches/pachauri-davos-january-2008.pdf</span></a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> (p.1)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn3"></a><a href="#_ftnref3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><a href="http://www.ipcc.ch/pdf/press-ar4/ipcc-flyer-low.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.ipcc.ch/pdf/press-ar4/ipcc-flyer-low.pdf</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn4"></a><a href="#_ftnref4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> Interview in </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">Nature Climate Change</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">published online</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">26 November 2013 </span><a href="http://www.nature.com/nclimate/journal/v3/n12/full/nclimate2064.html"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.nature.com/nclimate/journal/v3/n12/full/nclimate2064.html</span></a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn5"></a><a href="#_ftnref5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><a href="http://hcl.harvard.edu/collections/ipcc/index.html"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://hcl.harvard.edu/collections/ipcc/index.html</span></a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> and </span><a href="http://www.noaa.gov/foia/noaa_useful_websites/IPCC.html"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.noaa.gov/foia/noaa_useful_websites/IPCC.html</span></a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn6"></a><a href="#_ftnref6">[6]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><a href="http://climateaudit.org/2008/04/01/ipcc-review-editors-comments-online/"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://climateaudit.org/2008/04/01/ipcc-review-editors-comments-online/</span></a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn7"></a><a href="#_ftnref7">[7]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> The IAC Review is ava</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">ilable here: </span><a href="http://reviewipcc.interacademycouncil.net/"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://reviewipcc.interacademycouncil.net/</span></a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">The IAC Review’s recommendations on the representation of uncertainty, on conflict of interest policy, and on the establishment of an IPCC </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">E</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">xecutive Committee</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> with independent members</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> and the IPCC’s responses to those recommendations are also very pertinent to the Committee’s inquiry but are beyond the scope of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">my</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> submission</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn8"></a><a href="#_ftnref8">[8]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> This suggestion was not, however, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">one of the</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> formal recommendation</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">of</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> the IAC Review.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn9"></a><a href="#_ftnref9">[9]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><a href="http://www.ipcc.ch/organization/organization_review.shtml"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.ipcc.ch/organization/organization_review.shtml</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn10"></a><a href="#_ftnref10">[10]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> The 2013 version of </span><span style="font-